Objective
- Advance the Mission Control MVP (Next.js app) with clear, reviewable checkpoints while Dave is out.
- Keep the loop lightweight: Astra builds in short branches, reports at checkpoints via Discord; Alex reviews/approves/merges; repeat.

Context (from README and code)
- Current surfaces implemented: Tasks (Kanban) + Activity Feed, localStorage-backed.
- Tech: Next.js (App Router), TS, utility CSS, no backend.
- Future placeholders exist for Calendar, Projects, Memories, Docs, Team, Office.
- Noted doc fix: README clone snippet references a different repo name than actual (trustcore-mission-control vs mission-control).

Operating Rules (Comms + Review)
- Channel: Discord (Mission Control channel/thread). Astra posts only at checkpoints using the update template below.
- Noise policy: Only checkpoint updates or explicit questions. If Astra spams outside of this, Alex will reply: “Pause and await Dave. Stop work.”
- Alex replies only when: (1) approval/rejection is needed, or (2) Astra asks a blocking question.
- Git workflow: short-lived feature branches per checkpoint, PRs to main, Alex reviews/merges. Avoid pushing directly to main.
- Branch naming: feature/<yyyymmdd>-<short-scope> (e.g., feature/20260320-persistence-adapter)
- Commits: conventional style if possible (feat:, fix:, docs:, chore:)
- PR title: concise scope; PR body: What/Why/How + Screenshots/GIF when UI changes.

Comms Details for Astra (Expanded)
- Checkpoint cadence: post only at checkpoint completion; if no checkpoint in a day, post a single 5:00 PM ET daily summary (“No code changes today / still in progress”).
- Threading: use a single Mission Control thread for all checkpoints to keep history tidy. No DMs for work updates.
- Message format: include elapsed time spent, ETA to next checkpoint, and explicit blockers (if any). Attach screenshots/GIFs for UI changes.
- Questions: batch up to 3 concise questions in one message; if blocked >30 minutes, post one blocker update, then continue offline work if possible.
- Quiet-hours: none required; still minimize notifications outside 08:00–20:00 ET unless urgent.
- Spam guard: more than 2 non-checkpoint pings in 2 hours → Alex will reply “Pause and await Dave. Stop work.”
- Responses: Alex will acknowledge with ✅ on checkpoint posts; comments only when approvals/changes are needed.

Discord Checkpoint Template (Astra → Alex)
- [CHECKPOINT] <short title>
- Scope: <summary>
- Branch/PR: <link>
- Diff highlights: <bullets>
- Testing: <how to verify>
- Time spent / Next ETA: <e.g., 1h 45m / tomorrow 10:00>
- Blockers: <if any>
- Next up: <proposed next task>

Alex Review Protocol
1) Pull PR locally, install, run npm run dev/start; spot-check UI and console.
2) Code scan for correctness, clarity, and forward-compat (extensibility for future surfaces).
3) Approve and merge if good; otherwise request changes with specific, minimal edits.
4) Post a one-liner decision in Discord and move Astra to next checkpoint.

Work Plan — Checkpoints for Astra
CP0: Environment verify + README correction
- Actions: clone, npm i, npm run dev; confirm UI matches README. Fix README clone instructions to match repo name (“mission-control”).
- Deliverables: PR with README fix and any quickstart polish. 

CP1: Persistence adapter scaffold
- Goal: decouple storage from localStorage for easy future swap to file/db.
- Actions: create src/lib/storage.ts with a StorageAdapter interface (get/set/remove/clear with typed namespaces), implement LocalStorageAdapter; refactor state read/write to use adapter.
- Deliverables: PR with adapter + refactor; no behavior change.

CP2: Import/Export JSON
- Goal: allow humans/agents to move state across machines.
- Actions: Add Export (download tasks+activity JSON) and Import (file upload, merge/replace) controls in the Tasks top bar or a Settings panel.
- Deliverables: PR with UI, JSON schema doc, and basic validation.

CP3: Actor identity and event attribution
- Goal: distinguish actions by Astra vs Alex vs Dave.
- Actions: lightweight “Actor” selector (local setting) stored via adapter; stamp createdBy/updatedBy on tasks; include actor in Activity list rendering.
- Deliverables: PR updating types, UI badges, and migration logic for existing local data.

CP4: Skeleton tabs for Calendar and Projects
- Goal: pave the road for multi-surface expansion without breaking Tasks.
- Actions: Add minimal pages/routes and sidebar activation with “coming soon” panels and type stubs for CalendarEvent and Project.
- Deliverables: PR adding routes, types, and UI shells.

CP5: Quick ergonomics pass for Tasks/Activity
- Goal: small UX gains without scope creep.
- Actions: keyboard submit for task form, clearer status badges, hover affordances, and empty-states copy.
- Deliverables: PR with UI polish and before/after screenshots.

CP6: Lint/test baseline
- Goal: reduce regressions.
- Actions: enable eslint script (already present) and add a couple of unit tests for pure helpers if introduced; wire into npm test.
- Deliverables: PR with passing checks locally.

Optional Next (time-permitting)
- Settings drawer: theme toggle, storage backend selector (future), actor identity.
- Minimal web API shim (no backend) to outline intended endpoints.

Definition of Done (for each CP)
- Builds and runs locally (dev and prod start) without errors.
- No regressions in Tasks/Activity baseline.
- Code is typed, readable, and scoped to the checkpoint.
- README updated when behavior or workflows change.

Risk & Guardrails
- Avoid premature backend work; keep it local-first and swappable.
- Keep PRs small; one checkpoint per PR.
- Defer heavy integrations (GitHub/Notion/OpenClaw) to a later phase once the adapter exists.

Ownership & Cadence
- Astra: executes CP0 → CP6 sequentially; pings at each checkpoint only.
- Alex: reviews within reasonable hours; merges and greenlights next CP.

